        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 27:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; but it is not to be called in question on that account, as Knobel supposes. It is perfectly obvious from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 3:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". that all the details are not given in the historical account of the event referred to. כּל תּמוּנת פּסל, \"image of a form of all that Jehovah has commanded,\" sc., not to be made (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 4:16-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). \"A consuming fire\" (",
